features: Gaming PC Case features a pure aesthetic, flexible modes and configurations for a high-performing personal build. The solid and durable O11D EVO computer case is crafted from 4mm aluminum and 1mm steel structure. The 4mm dark tinted tempered glass panels make it easy to show the RGB components and your personalities

Computer Case with Optimized Cooling & Modular Design – The top mesh panel is upgraded with optimal airflow and dust filtering ratio. By using optional kits, there are many configuration choices for air and water cooling. Sufficient space to accommodate 3x 360mm radiators, and up to 10 fans

Desktop PC Case with Ample Drive Space - Offers multiple storage drive mounting spaces that support up to 9x SSDs or 6x HDDs + 3x SSDs. You can remove the drive cage to make room for a second PSU or relocate it to a lower position. Thanks to the roomy interior, it is compatible with most of the current 4090 CPU video cards

Grey/Black Case with Effortless Cable Management - Cable management is hassle-free within the O11D EVO thanks to its dual-chamber design and removable bracket. Removal I/O module includes 2 x USB 3.0, 1 x USB 3.1 TYPE-C and 1 x HD AUDIO/ MIC port. The Harbor Grey is Micro Center’s exclusive model

Mid Tower E-ATX Computer Chassis. Large PC case dimensions: 465mm x 285mm x 459mm (18.3inch x 11.2inch x 18.1inch), Weight: 13.2kg/ 29.1 lbs. Wide motherboard compatibility: supports E-ATX (width: under 280mm)/ATX /M-ATX/ITX. Mid-tower chassis with two modes: Normal Mode/ Reverse Mode

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Keep cool with the O11 Dynamic series all-new design that allows you to personalize your build.

Versatile Orientation With only a few steps, the O11D EVO can be flipped in reverse mode to experience a seamless front and side tempered glass showroom view on the right side of the chassis. Exquisite, Yet Functional Following the style of the O11 Dynamic series, the aluminum panels feature an updated fine mesh which provides an optimal ratio of airflow and dust filtering. Relocatable I/O Port At the bottom of the chassis, the I/O module can be relocated to 3 different locations without the use of tools. Personalized ARGB Lighting Strip The front panel LED strip features 7 built-in lighting effects which can be controlled via the M button. An 8th mode is available to enable motherboard software synchronization or L-Connect control.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great all around case, easy to build in!
reviews.reviewText: If you're looking for a PC case for your next build, look no further, this has tons of room for cable management and I found it very easy to put everything together in this case. Even had enough room for my ASUS ROG Strix 4090, which is the biggest GPU I have ever seen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful case with lots of space
reviews.reviewText: I got this case to build my new compy. I was interested in it because of the airflow and the expansion bays. 9 SSD's sound excessive, but as someone who has 5 drives - 4 of them SSD's it was a major draw. installation is clear and easy. Cable management is beautiful and hidden. Airflow is perfect. This case has it all and is large enough that I see myself able to expand a few times before I have to upgrade out of this case

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Building in this thing was super easy. Had plenty of room to fit a 4080 gpu. Looks so clean. Huge fan of lian li now!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent case all around with no complaints
reviews.reviewText: This is definitely a premium case in every sense, the layout, materials, and quality are all top notch. A joy to work with outside of how much it weighs, but it weighs as much as it does due to the thick metal they use so that may as well be a compliment. Personally I appreciate the matte finish of the Harbor Grey over the brushed metal texture of the other variants.The only thing to note is that the tint on this Harbor Grey model is rather aggressive. Personally that's what I wanted as it allows some rather bright LEDs to show up without being too visually loud and I think it looks clean, but if you don't run much lighting you'll struggle to see inside unless you game in direct sunlight.If I had to make a single complaint it'd be that I'm not a fan of the grey rubber grommets in the case as I'd prefer them to be black, but they're not especially prominent and the tint makes them harder to spot as well. This is pretty much my singular problem with the case, and it doesn't even matter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great tower for display
reviews.reviewText: With the tinted glass you can hardly see anything inside when it’s off, but when it turns on everything lights up beautifully. Didn’t originally care for the tinted glass at first but after everything was done and it was time to pick a chassis for a second build it was hard to find an equal. I actually had to settle for a close second due to the fact I don’t want two identical builds. More then enough room for cable management and concealing cables that may not be in use if you don’t have a modular PSU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: SFX PSU, ATX MOBO, and FULL sized GPU. Thermals are great and support for watercooling is easy. My only issue is the 2.5 HDD support the bottom screw was stripped when I got it. Bottom fan filter slides out from the left side and the top and vertical fan filters are magnetic <3.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You need this case.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. My pc was crammed into a cyber power case and was overheating a lot. I could not fit a 360AIO in the case to help with cooling, So I decided to get a new case. I have never built a pc (mine was custom ordered online) but when I tell you this was one of the easiest thing I’ve done I’m not joking. This case is literally exactly what I needed. Aio fit and my pc temps have never been better.Cable management: 5/5Case build quality: 5/5Room for future upgrades: 5/5Airflow/cooling: 5/5Appearance: 5/5 (I got the grey)the case came with bushings for mounting fans and other stuff, which cut down on vibration and sound by ridiculous amounts. If there weren’t lights inside I would never be able to tell it was on or off.Which brings me to The one and only thing I can say I do not like about the case. It is how dark the front glass is. It is bright at night but during the daytime you can hardly see the inside of the case. But that does not interfere with my love for the case. If you are debating on buying. Dooooo it you will not regret it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Case is gorgeous in the Harbor Gray I got it in, but I’m sure it looks just as amazing in any other color it comes in. Very easy to install and a lot more spacious than it looks. It can hold my 4090 FE as shown in the pic. It also comes with a lot of extras for any build you might be thinking about. Lian Li is da G.O.A.T. I highly recommend you watch a video review of this case so you know the easy way to take it apart. It’s not very long as it’s very simple to do.

reviews.reviewTitle: MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi doesn't fit well
reviews.reviewText: MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi doesn't fit well into the case. There are not enough space near the ports so it's needed to apply much force to fit motherboard with the screw holes.

reviews.reviewTitle: great case with exceptional looks. easily the best case I have used in over 40 years of PCs
reviews.reviewText: Fitted a 360mm All-in-One Vetroo cooler and 10 Uphere fans (also from Amazon) with no problems.
